<h1>Deduplication of Flock audit logs</h1>

<h2>Problem</h2>

<p>Flock audit logs record one row per network queried. When an officer searches multiple networks in one session (e.g., querying 3 camera networks), 3 rows appear. The deduplication step merges these into a single "search session."</p>

<h2>Method</h2>

<p>Rows are grouped by: officer name, organization name, reason, case number, and time window. Rows that share all these fields are merged into one session. The <code>Networks Queried</code> field records how many networks were hit.</p>

<h2>Result</h2>

<p>2,007 raw rows → 1,572 unique search sessions.</p>

